166
00:11:56,466 --> 00:12:00,761
They loved you. I told
you they would love you,
and they loved you.

167
00:12:00,929 --> 00:12:04,306
I love you.
I love you, Walter.

168
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:09,311
Did anyone ever call you
anything other than Walter?

169
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:10,646
No.

170
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:17,152
Not even when you were young?
No, not even when I was young.

171
00:12:18,113 --> 00:12:19,947
You sure you don't want to drive with me?

172
00:12:20,115 --> 00:12:22,825
Oh, how will I get back to Baltimore on Friday?

173
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:27,162
I forgot the present. Walter,
I left your stepmother's
present inside by accident.

174
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:28,914
I swear, when we're old and grey

175
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:30,916
you gonna have to remind me to put my teeth in.

176
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:35,295
I'll be walking all over
town smacking my gums
together, not even noticing.

177
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:38,382
I'll wait.
You'll wait? Oh, right.

178
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:41,468
No, don't wait, Walter.
Really, it's silly, you go ahead.
We're late anyway.

179
