211
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:06,178
JONAH: It's not for me, it's for my dad.
I think he needs a new wife.

212
00:14:06,638 --> 00:14:08,430
FIELDSTONE:
You don't like the one he has now?

213
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:10,891
JONAH:
He doesn't have one now.
That's the problem.

214
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:12,601
FIELDSTONE:
Where's your mum?

215
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:14,102
JONAH:
She died.

216
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:18,440
FIELDSTONE: Oh, I'm so sorry.
Well, who can believe this?

217
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:21,401
JONAH: I've been pretty sad,
but I think my Dad's worse.

218
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,404
FIELDSTONE:
Have you talked to your dad about it?

219
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,323
JONAH: No.
FIELDSTONE: Why not?

220
00:14:26,491 --> 00:14:28,408
JONAH:
It's like it makes him sadder.

221
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:32,079
FIELDSTONE:
Aw, I can understand that.
Jonah, is your dad home right now?

222
00:14:32,247 --> 00:14:34,498
JONAH: Yeah.
What's he doing? Is he busy?

223
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:36,708
JONAH:
Not really, he's out on the deck.

224
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:41,046
