FIELDSTONE:
Trust me, Jonah.

227
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:52,099
He won't be angry when he realises
how concerned you are about him.

228
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,308
Wanna bet?

229
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:56,103
JONAH:
But if I get yelled at, I'm never
gonna listen to your show again.

230
00:14:56,271 --> 00:14:57,521
FIELDSTONE:
Okay, fair enough.

231
00:14:59,649 --> 00:15:02,109
JONAH: Dad?
SAM: Yeah.

232
00:15:02,277 --> 00:15:05,362
JONAH: There's someone
on the phone for you.

233
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:10,909
His name is Sam.
FIELDSTONE: Sam.

234
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:13,495
If you've just tuned in,
this is Dr. Marcia Fieldstone

235
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:16,206
and tonight's topic is your wishes and dreams.

236
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:17,416
I got it.

237
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:19,167
We're on the line now with someone from Seattle.

238
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:20,377
Hello.

239
00:15:20,545 --> 00:15:24,298
Hello, Sam, this is Dr. Fieldstone
on Network America.

240
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:29,720
Okay. What are you selling tonight?
Micro-hibachis or knives?

241
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:33,015
FIELDSTONE:
No, I'm not selling anything.
I just wanna help.

242
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,100
I want you to know that your son called

243
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:38,687
and he asked me for some advice
on how you might find a new wife.

244
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:40,188
Who is this?

245
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:46,153
Dr. Marcia Fieldstone
of Network America.
And you are on the air.

246
00:15:46,321 --> 00:15:50,490
You called a radio station?
FIELDSTONE: Sam, are you with me?

247
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:51,992
Yeah. Yes.

248
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,663
Your son feels that
since your wife's death
you've been very, very unhappy.

249
00:15:56,831 --> 00:16:00,334
And he is genuinely worried about you.

250
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:05,088
Get out here. Get out here.
Come on, now, I'm not
gonna go through this alone.

251
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:09,426
I think it's very hard for him
to talk to you about all this.

252
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:14,348
I thought maybe you and I
could talk, it would make Jonah
feel a little better. Sam?

253
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:18,018
Talk to her, Dad. She's a doctor.
Of what?

254
00:16:18,186 --> 00:16:19,770
Her first name could be Doctor.

255
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:26,610
Please.
Sam. Sam, it's his Christmas wish.

256
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:29,821
Okay.
Okay. Good.

257
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:35,243
FIELDSTONE:
Now, I know this is difficult.
But how long ago did your wife die?

258
00:16:36,287 --> 00:16:41,833
About a year and a half ago.
Aw. Have you had any relationships?

259
00:16:42,669 --> 00:16:47,047
No.
No? Why not?

260
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:52,886
Uh, Marcia, or Dr. Fieldstone?
Dr. Marcia.

261
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:57,057
Dr. Marcia.
SAM: I don't mean to be rude...

262
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,226
FIELDSTONE:
And I don't want to invade
your privacy...

263
00:16:59,394 --> 00:17:00,977
Sure you do.
SAM: Sure you do.

264
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:06,149
FIELDSTONE:
Go on, Sam. I'm listening. Sam.

265
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:12,197
We had a pretty tough time at first.

266
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:15,075
But we're dealing with it.

267
00:17:15,410 --> 00:17:22,082
And Jonah and I will
get along just fine again,
as soon as I break his radio.

268
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,543
[FIELDSTONE LAUGHING]

269
00:17:24,711 --> 00:17:27,754
FIELDSTONE: I have no doubt that
you're a wonderful father.

270
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:30,382
You know, you can tell a lot
from a person's voice.

271
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:31,842
You certainly can.

272
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:36,263
But something must be missing
if Jonah still feels
that you're under a cloud.

273
00:17:36,431 --> 00:17:39,015
Just a few questions:
Are you sleeping at night?

274
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,810
JONAH:
He doesn't sleep at all.

275
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:44,730
How do you know that?
I live here, Dad.

276
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:51,778
Look, it's Christmas.

277
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:59,327
Maggie, my wife.

278
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:02,497
She really did it...

279
00:18:02,665 --> 00:18:07,335
I mean, she loved...
She made everything beautiful.

280
00:18:09,464 --> 00:18:13,300
It's just tough this time of year.

281
00:18:13,468 --> 00:18:15,051
Every kid needs a mother.

282
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:20,724
Could it be that you need someone
just as much as Jonah does?

283
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:25,353
Yes.
FIELDSTONE: Don't answer that.

284
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:27,522
Let's get into that right after these messages.

285
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:29,941
Sam, Jonah, don't go away.

286
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:34,362
If you've have just tuned in,
we are talking to Sleepless in Seattle.

287
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:38,533
And we'll be right back
after this break
with your listener response.

288
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:40,494
What is she talking about?

289
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:43,246
This is when other people
get to call in and dump
on what you said.

290
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:49,211
Oh. Oh. Well, this is
really fun. And helpful.

291
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,302
WOMAN:
I bet he's tall
with a cute butt.

292
00:18:57,470 --> 00:18:59,846
WAITRESS 1:
I bet he hasn't bathed
in weeks and he stinks.

293
00:19:00,014 --> 00:19:04,100
Harriet, shut up. Hi, can I help you?
Tea, with the bag out.

294
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:08,313
You know, maybe I'll just go
up to Seattle, give him
a little gift for New Year's Eve.

295
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:11,608
WAITRESS 2: Yeah, you go on
out there if you want to.
