00:19:29,794 --> 00:19:34,422
WOMAN: Yes, I would just like
to know where I could
get this man's address.

303
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,466
Honey, get in line.

304
00:19:36,634 --> 00:19:38,468
FIELDSTONE:
Next caller, go ahead.

305
00:19:39,637 --> 00:19:43,640
FIELDSTONE:
If there was one question
I was allowed to ask...

306
00:19:43,808 --> 00:19:44,933
Oh, go ahead.

307
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:49,229
People who truly loved once
are far more likely to love again.

308
00:19:49,397 --> 00:19:54,025
Sam, do you think that there is
someone out there you could love
as much as your wife?

309
00:19:56,863 --> 00:20:01,157
Well, Dr. Marcia Fieldstone,
that's hard to imagine.

310
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:04,452
What are you going to do?

311
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:08,874
Well, I'm going to get out of bed every morning

312
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,835
and breathe in and out all day long.

313
00:20:12,503 --> 00:20:16,965
And after a while I won't have to remind myself

314
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:20,969
to get out of bed every morning
and breathe in and out.

315
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:25,181
And then after a while I won't
have to think about

316
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:30,228
how I had it great and perfect for a while.

317
00:20:30,438 --> 00:20:34,691
FIELDSTONE:
Sam, tell me what was
so special about your wife.

318
00:20:34,859 --> 00:20:37,360
SAM:
Well, how long is your programme?

319
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:45,243
Oh, well, it was a million tiny, little things.

320
00:20:45,411 --> 00:20:50,081
When you added them all up,
it just meant we were
supposed to be together.

321
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:54,628
And I knew it, I knew it
the very first time I touched her.

322
00:20:55,212 --> 00:21:00,717
It was like coming home,
only to no home I'd ever known.

323
00:21:00,885 --> 00:21:04,179
I was just taking her hand

324
00:21:04,347 --> 00:21:08,975
to help her out of a car.
And I knew it.

325
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:14,814
It was like magic.
Magic.

326
00:21:15,608 --> 00:21:21,321
FIELDSTONE: Well, folks, it's time
to wrap it up. I'm Dr. Marcia
Fieldstone in Chicago.

327
00:21:21,489 --> 00:21:25,825
And to all my listeners,
a magical and merry Christmas.

328
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:29,371
And to you, Sleepless in Seattle,

329
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:33,249
we hope you'll call again soon
and let us know how it's going.

