00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:49,909
Two thousand women
called the station asking
for the guy's number.

344
00:22:50,077 --> 00:22:53,705
I heard it. This kid
calls up and says,
"My dad needs a wife."

345
00:22:53,873 --> 00:22:57,250
And the shrink practically forces
the guy and says,
"Do you want to talk about it."

346
00:22:57,418 --> 00:22:59,544
And he says,
"No, as a matter of fact, I don't."

347
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:02,547
And then suddenly
for no reason at all
he start to talk

348
00:23:02,715 --> 00:23:03,882
about how much he loved his wife

349
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:07,302
and how he just fell in love
with her like he was one
of those cows in Michigan.

350
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:09,429
What cows in Michigan?

351
00:23:09,597 --> 00:23:12,807
It was on 60 Minutes
over those cows that got
zapped by stray voltage.

352
00:23:12,975 --> 00:23:15,101
No one knows why.
And maybe it was Wisconsin.

353
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:19,814
But, anyway, I was listening
to him talk about how much
he loved his wife

354
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,733
and suddenly I was crying.

355
00:23:22,109 --> 00:23:24,360
It's like what happens
when I watch those
phone company ads.

356
00:23:24,528 --> 00:23:26,362
I don't have to see
the whole thing,
just the part

357
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:29,824
where the daughter gives
the mother the refrigerator
with the big red bow.

358
00:23:29,992 --> 00:23:34,079
