800
00:53:39,967 --> 00:53:41,926
Fine.
How do I look?

801
00:53:42,094 --> 00:53:45,305
Great.
Do I look okay? I look all right?

802
00:53:45,472 --> 00:53:48,308
I look stupid. I
look stupid. I look like
I'm trying too hard.

803
00:53:48,475 --> 00:53:51,060
I was gonna get a haircut,
but I'd just look like
I got a haircut.

804
00:53:51,228 --> 00:53:54,606
This is a good letter, Dad.
The heels on these are grotesque.

805
00:53:54,773 --> 00:53:58,192
I look like I'm trying to be tall.
Her name is Annie Reed.

806
00:53:58,360 --> 00:54:01,029
SAM: Now I'm late. Bye.
Dad, read this.

807
00:54:01,238 --> 00:54:02,780
Read this!

808
00:54:04,825 --> 00:54:06,534
"Sleepless and Son...

809
00:54:06,702 --> 00:54:08,161
[MUMBLING]

810
00:54:08,787 --> 00:54:13,499
I've been an excellent
third baseman, and while
we're on it, let's just say right now:

811
00:54:13,667 --> 00:54:16,169
Brooks Robinson
was the best
third-base men ever.

812
00:54:16,337 --> 00:54:18,588
It's important you agree
with me on that because
I'm from Baltimore."

813
00:54:18,756 --> 00:54:21,299
She thinks Brooks
Robinson is the greatest.
