That's not true.

918
01:01:20,761 --> 01:01:21,886
FIELDSTONE:
Okay, now think.

919
01:01:22,054 --> 01:01:26,182
Shouldn't your father be
the judge of whether someone
is right or wrong for him?

920
01:01:26,350 --> 01:01:28,642
JONAH:
He's not sane enough
to judge anything.

921
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:34,690
Now he's kissing her on the lips.
My dad's been captured by a ho!
What am I going to do?

922
01:01:34,858 --> 01:01:39,570
FIELDSTONE: Jonah, calm down.
Tomorrow, when you're
sitting down to breakfast,

923
01:01:39,738 --> 01:01:45,618
tell him how you feel.
It's not good to keep
your feelings inside you.

924
01:01:45,786 --> 01:01:48,204
[SCREAMS]

925
01:01:50,165 --> 01:01:54,752
Miss Scarlet.
In the broom closet.
With the radio.

926
01:01:54,920 --> 01:01:59,799
Walter, you scared me.
Don't ever do that again.

927
01:02:03,345 --> 01:02:05,262
I thought I saw a black widow spider.

928
01:02:05,430 --> 01:02:08,099
You scared me to death.
You scared Victoria to death.

929
01:02:08,266 --> 01:02:09,350
It was right over there.

930
01:02:09,518 --> 01:02:13,437
Next time you think you see
a black widow spider
I want you to say:

931
01:02:13,605 --> 01:02:17,691
"Dad, excuse me,
but I believe a poisonous insect
is in the house."

932
01:02:17,859 --> 01:02:21,320
And I will calmly come
and take care of it. You scream
like that again, I'll kill you.

933
01:02:21,488 --> 01:02:24,281
Becky heard this guy
on the radio, she was
sure it was Rick.

934
01:02:24,449 --> 01:02:25,825
She was completely hysterical.

935
01:02:25,992 --> 01:02:31,539
And then it turned out
the guy lived in Duluth.
Where's Duluth?

936
01:02:32,249 --> 01:02:33,374
That doesn't make any sense.

937
01:02:33,542 --> 01:02:36,710
I know. I know, Walter.
It doesn't make any sense at all.

938
01:02:36,878 --> 01:02:42,591
Thank God my life is in place.
Duluth? That's in North Dakota.

939
01:02:43,969 --> 01:02:45,928
[♪♪♪]

940
01:02:56,940 --> 01:02:59,900
I love this letter.
You have to write to her.

941
01:03:00,068 --> 01:03:01,861
You think so?

942
01:03:02,028 --> 01:03:05,614
It's Y-O-H.
Yeah. What's that?

943
01:03:05,782 --> 01:03:07,533
Your only hope.

944
01:03:07,784 --> 01:03:09,493
[♪♪♪]

945
01:03:19,254 --> 01:03:24,675
I thought I would look into doing
a story on those radio shows.

946
01:03:24,843 --> 01:03:27,219
You'd have to go somewhere
to really look into them.

947
01:03:27,387 --> 01:03:29,472
Definitely.

948
01:03:48,366 --> 01:03:52,745
Couldn't you do a phone interview?
Not for the kind of piece I wanna do.

949
01:03:52,913 --> 01:03:57,208
I won't be in Chicago long.
When you get back, I'll be gone.

950
01:03:57,375 --> 01:04:01,504
Then I'll see you in New York.
I'll get it.

951
01:04:05,675 --> 01:04:10,763
PILOT [OVER PA]:
This is Captain Browning.
We're cruising at 35,000 feet.

952
01:04:10,931 --> 01:04:16,393
The weather is clear to the west
and we'll be in Seattle on schedule.

953
01:04:16,561 --> 01:04:19,188
Don't you hate flying?
Yes, I do.

954
01:04:19,356 --> 01:04:24,443
And I've just told the most terrible
one to the man I'm about to marry.

955
01:04:24,611 --> 01:04:27,905
Do you feel that any lie is a betrayal?

956
01:04:28,073 --> 01:04:31,909
I said flying.
Oh.

957
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:34,328
[SIGHS]

958
01:04:38,250 --> 01:04:42,670
Thanks for bringing me here.
Well, he likes the planes.

959
01:04:42,837 --> 01:04:45,047
Can I bring something
back for you? A souvenir?

960
01:04:45,215 --> 01:04:46,757
Does he like those little snow globes?

961
01:04:46,925 --> 01:04:49,635
You know, you shake them up
and then the snow floats down.

962
01:04:49,803 --> 01:04:53,639
Sure, I'd really like that.
Thank you so much.

963
01:04:57,227 --> 01:04:59,687
He's 8.
He's good at it.

964
01:04:59,854 --> 01:05:03,482
I've read an article about
this. Children are hideous
at the age of 8.

965
01:05:03,650 --> 01:05:04,900
It's quite normal.
Well...

966
01:05:05,068 --> 01:05:07,695
Maybe when I come back, the two of us

967
01:05:07,862 --> 01:05:12,032
ought to spend some time
together on our own.
What do you think?

968
01:05:16,538 --> 01:05:19,039
Bye. Bye, Jonah.

969
01:05:19,207 --> 01:05:20,541
Bye.

970
01:05:24,921 --> 01:05:27,131
Jonah.

971
01:05:27,299 --> 01:05:30,801
Listen to me.
You don't know Victoria.

972
01:05:30,969 --> 01:05:36,098
I hardly know her myself.
She's, in fact, a mystery to me.

973
01:05:36,266 --> 01:05:38,851
She tosses her hair a lot.
Why does she do this?

974
01:05:39,019 --> 01:05:42,896
I have no idea. Is it a twitch?
Does she need a haircut?

975
01:05:43,064 --> 01:05:45,482
Could she use a barrette
to keep her hair out of her face?

976
01:05:47,110 --> 01:05:50,237
These are the things I'm
willing to get to the bottom of.

977
01:05:50,405 --> 01:05:54,533
That is why I am dating her.

978
01:05:54,701 --> 01:06:00,080
That's all I'm doing.
I'm not living with her.
I'm not marrying her.

979
01:06:00,248 --> 01:06:03,792
Can you appreciate the difference?

980
01:06:03,960 --> 01:06:08,589
This is what single people do.
They try other people on
and see how they fit.

981
01:06:08,757 --> 01:06:14,845
But everybody's an adjustment.
Nobody's perfect.
There's no such thing as a perfect...

982
01:06:15,889 --> 01:06:17,890
[♪♪♪]

983
01:06:30,695 --> 01:06:32,613
Come on.

984
01:06:34,824 --> 01:06:38,035
Dad, I was talking to
Jessica about reincarnation.

985
01:06:38,203 --> 01:06:40,204
She says you knew Annie in another life.

986
01:06:40,372 --> 01:06:43,707
SAM: Who's Annie?
The one who wrote us.

987
01:06:43,875 --> 01:06:46,377
But Jessica says, you and Annie
never got together in that life.

988
01:06:46,544 --> 01:06:49,588
So your hearts are like
puzzles with missing pieces.

989
01:06:49,756 --> 01:06:51,215
And when you get together,
the puzzle's complete.

990
01:06:51,383 --> 01:06:53,008
Goddamn it.

991
01:06:53,176 --> 01:06:54,885
The reason I know this and you don't,

992
01:06:55,053 --> 01:06:59,473
is because I'm younger and
pure, so I'm more in touch
with cosmic forces.

993
01:06:59,641 --> 01:07:00,974
Who told you this stuff?

994
01:07:01,142 --> 01:07:02,184
Jessica.

995
01:07:02,352 --> 01:07:05,187
I sincerely hope you're not marrying Jessica.

996
01:07:05,605 --> 01:07:09,024
