01:07:11,611 --> 01:07:15,739
♪ <i>I remember the days</i> ♪
♪ <i>Of just keeping time</i> ♪

998
01:07:16,157 --> 01:07:21,704
♪ <i>Of hanging around</i> ♪
♪ <i>In sleepy towns forever</i> ♪

999
01:07:22,831 --> 01:07:26,125
♪ <i>Back roads empty for miles</i> ♪

1000
01:07:28,753 --> 01:07:32,840
♪ <i>Well, you can't have a dream</i> ♪
♪ <i>And cut it to fit</i> ♪

1001
01:07:33,508 --> 01:07:36,343
♪ <i>But when I saw you, I knew</i> ♪

1002
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:42,641
♪ <i>We'd go together</i> ♪
♪ <i>Like a wink and a smile</i> ♪

1003
01:07:46,771 --> 01:07:49,857
♪ <i>Leave your old jalopy</i> ♪

1004
01:07:50,650 --> 01:07:53,652
♪ <i>By the railroad track</i> ♪

1005
01:07:55,071 --> 01:07:58,741
♪ <i>We'll get a hip double-dip tip-toppy</i> ♪

1006
01:07:59,284 --> 01:08:02,369
♪ <i>Two-seat Pontiac</i> ♪

1007
01:08:04,789 --> 01:08:09,334
♪ <i>So you can rev her up</i> ♪
♪ <i>Don't go slow</i> ♪

1008
01:08:09,544 --> 01:08:12,838
♪ <i>It's only green lights and all rights</i> ♪

1009
01:08:13,339 --> 01:08:19,178
♪ <i>Let's go together</i> ♪
♪ <i>With a wink and a smile</i> ♪

1010
01:08:33,818 --> 01:08:36,737
♪ <i>Give me a wink and a smile</i> ♪

1011
01:08:48,792 --> 01:08:53,128
♪ <i>We go together</i> ♪
♪ <i>Like a wink and a smile</i> ♪

1012
01:08:57,383 --> 01:09:00,219
♪ <i>Now my heart is music</i> ♪

1013
01:09:00,845 --> 01:09:04,014
♪ <i>Such a simple song</i> ♪

1014
01:09:05,433 --> 01:09:09,061
♪ <i>Sing it again</i> ♪
♪ <i>The notes never end</i> ♪

1015
01:09:09,771 --> 01:09:12,773
♪ <i>This is where I belong</i> ♪

1016
01:09:13,608 --> 01:09:15,651
♪ <i>Just the sound of your voice</i> ♪

1017
01:09:15,902 --> 01:09:17,694
♪ <i>The light in your eyes</i> ♪

1018
01:09:18,196 --> 01:09:21,990
♪ <i>We're so far away from yesterday</i> ♪

1019
01:09:22,492 --> 01:09:28,413
♪ <i>Together with a wink and a smile</i> ♪

1020
01:09:31,251 --> 01:09:33,919
♪ <i>We go together</i> ♪

1021
01:09:35,004 --> 01:09:38,966
♪ <i>Like a wink and a smile</i> ♪♪

1022
01:09:48,852 --> 01:09:51,562
ANNIE:
I watched him play with
his son at the beach.

1023
01:09:51,729 --> 01:09:53,689
BECKY [ON PHONE]:
Did you talk to him?

1024
01:09:53,857 --> 01:09:55,816
Couldn't do it.

1025
01:09:57,610 --> 01:09:59,069
How did I get here?

1026
01:09:59,237 --> 01:10:01,196
You told a lie and got on a plane.

1027
01:10:01,364 --> 01:10:03,574
That's not what I mean.

1028
01:10:04,534 --> 01:10:06,702
I'm going back over there tomorrow

1029
01:10:06,870 --> 01:10:08,412
and talk to him. I am.

1030
01:10:08,580 --> 01:10:12,416
Okay. Good. Goodbye.
Beck.

1031
01:10:12,584 --> 01:10:14,376
What?

1032
01:10:16,170 --> 01:10:20,799
Is this crazy?
No, that's the weirdest part about it.

1033
01:10:21,885 --> 01:10:25,721
Thank you. I love you.
I love you too.

1034
01:10:25,889 --> 01:10:28,015
Good night.
Bye.

1035
01:10:28,641 --> 01:10:39,318
[♪♪♪]

1036
01:11:23,237 --> 01:11:24,696
[GIGGLING]

1037
01:11:30,703 --> 01:11:33,497
It's so good to see you.
Where's Greg?

1038
01:11:35,583 --> 01:11:36,917
[HORN HONKING]

1039
01:11:45,927 --> 01:11:47,469
[♪♪♪]

1040
01:11:57,897 --> 01:12:02,275
Hello.

1041
01:12:05,154 --> 01:12:06,405
[HORN HONKING]

1042
01:12:08,658 --> 01:12:11,994
BECKY: So then what happened?
ANNIE: So then I left, obviously.

1043
01:12:13,204 --> 01:12:15,247
You were standing in the middle of the street?

1044
01:12:15,415 --> 01:12:18,834
You know that dream when you're
walking down the street naked
and everyone is looking at you.

1045
01:12:19,127 --> 01:12:20,502
I love that dream.

1046
01:12:20,670 --> 01:12:24,798
That was nothing compared
to this humiliation. Nothing!

1047
01:12:24,966 --> 01:12:26,883
But he saw you, right?
He saw me.

1048
01:12:27,051 --> 01:12:30,137
You were face to face.
He said hello.

1049
01:12:30,304 --> 01:12:31,680
He said hello.
And what did you say?

1050
01:12:31,848 --> 01:12:36,018
And all I could say was hello.
Oh, my God.

1051
01:12:36,936 --> 01:12:42,524
KERR: All I could say was hello.
It's a sign.

1052
01:12:42,692 --> 01:12:47,821
It's a sign that I have watched
this movie too many times.

1053
01:12:47,989 --> 01:12:51,742
So stupid! From the minute
I listened to that stupid programme

1054
01:12:51,909 --> 01:12:54,619
on the radio, I've been a complete jerk.

1055
01:12:54,787 --> 01:12:58,665
You are not a jerk.
Thank you. An idiot!

1056
01:12:58,833 --> 01:13:02,794
You don't know who she was, Annie.
I saw her. I have a picture of her.

1057
01:13:02,962 --> 01:13:04,337
I'll show you a picture of her.

1058
01:13:04,505 --> 01:13:07,299
That detective in Seattle
sent me a picture of her.

1059
01:13:07,467 --> 01:13:11,094
Here! See, that's
exactly what she looks like.

1060
01:13:11,971 --> 01:13:14,431
This is a picture of someone's back.

1061
01:13:14,599 --> 01:13:17,100
Well, it's her and he was crazy about her.

1062
01:13:17,268 --> 01:13:21,104
What's this?
This is from Seattle.

1063
01:13:29,238 --> 01:13:31,948
Becky.

1064
01:13:33,034 --> 01:13:36,495
So I mailed your letter.

1065
01:13:37,205 --> 01:13:41,208
"Dear Annie.
Thanks for your letter.
It was great.

1066
01:13:41,375 --> 01:13:43,251
You sound neat.

1067
01:13:46,547 --> 01:13:52,886
We're very excited about meeting
you in New York on Valentine's Day
and seeing if we are...

1068
01:13:53,054 --> 01:13:56,348
M-F-E-O.

1069
01:13:56,516 --> 01:14:00,727
See you soon.
Sleepless in Seattle."

1070
01:14:00,895 --> 01:14:03,688
M-F-E-O?

1071
01:14:06,734 --> 01:14:08,735
Made for each other.

1072
01:14:10,530 --> 01:14:13,698
It's cute. It's like a little clue.

1073
01:14:16,577 --> 01:14:17,911
[SCREAMS]

1074
01:14:18,287 --> 01:14:21,665
So he can't write. Big deal.

1075
01:14:21,833 --> 01:14:24,292
Verbal ability is a highly
overrated thing in a guy.

1076
01:14:24,460 --> 01:14:27,504
And our pathetic need
for it is what gets us
into so much trouble.

1077
01:14:27,672 --> 01:14:31,258
I'm going to run back
to Walter's arms,
if he'll still have me.

1078
01:14:31,425 --> 01:14:32,717
What about the letter?

1079
01:14:32,885 --> 01:14:37,681
It's nothing. It was written before
I went out there. Before the ho.

1080
01:14:40,309 --> 01:14:43,687
The only thing is, she didn't look like a ho.

1081
01:14:43,855 --> 01:14:47,315
She looked like
somebody we would
have been friends with.

1082
01:14:48,985 --> 01:14:50,360
Ugh!

1083
01:14:51,028 --> 01:14:53,488
You saw her in the airport and then here?

1084
01:14:53,656 --> 01:14:56,658
And I tried to talk to her.
It was like I knew her
or something. It was weird.

1085
01:14:56,826 --> 01:14:58,368
You mean like a déjà-vu thing?

1086
01:14:58,536 --> 01:15:01,746
It was very French déjà-vu-ish
kind of thing. Oui?

1087
01:15:01,914 --> 01:15:06,042
Oui. At least you're out there seeing
people again. That's terrific.

1088
01:15:06,210 --> 01:15:08,253
Well, I mean, there's really just the one.

1089
01:15:08,421 --> 01:15:12,549
Victoria.
You don't like Victoria?

1090
01:15:12,717 --> 01:15:15,760
She laughs like a hyena.
Is this true?

1091
01:15:15,928 --> 01:15:17,220
No!

1092
01:15:17,388 --> 01:15:21,099
Sort of. Yeah, a little bit.
But, tell them what you did.

1093
01:15:21,309 --> 01:15:22,934
Dad...
SAM: Tell them about the radio show.

1094
01:15:23,102 --> 01:15:24,144
Go ahead.
Dad...

1095
01:15:24,312 --> 01:15:25,979
They wanna hear it.
Go ahead. Tell them.
Tell them.

1096
01:15:26,147 --> 01:15:29,691
Christmas Eve, he phones in
one of those radio call-in shows.

1097
01:15:29,859 --> 01:15:34,571
And tells them I need a new wife.
Oh, you're kidding.

1098
01:15:34,739 --> 01:15:36,740
That's so sweet.

1099
01:15:36,908 --> 01:15:39,701
Now he's obsessed with
this one woman who wrote me.

1100
01:15:39,869 --> 01:15:40,952
Are you serious?
Yeah.

1101
01:15:41,120 --> 01:15:43,747
She wants to meet me
at the top of Empire
State Building.

1102
01:15:43,956 --> 01:15:46,374
On Valentine's Day.

1103
01:15:46,542 --> 01:15:49,085
It's like that movie.
What movie?

1104
01:15:49,253 --> 01:15:52,172
An Affair to Remember.
Did you ever see it?

1105
01:15:52,340 --> 01:15:57,469
Oh, God. Cary Grant
and Deborah Kerr.
Is that "Karr" or "Kerr"?

1106
01:15:57,637 --> 01:15:59,221
Kerr.
Karr.

1107
01:15:59,388 --> 01:16:03,391
Okay. She's gonna meet him
at the top of the Empire
State Building.

1108
01:16:03,559 --> 01:16:06,228
Only she got hit by a taxi.

1109
01:16:06,395 --> 01:16:11,566
And he waited and waited.
And it was raining, I think.

1110
01:16:11,734 --> 01:16:18,198
And then she's too proud
to tell him that she's...

1111
01:16:20,576 --> 01:16:26,456
crippled. And he's too proud
to find out why she doesn't come.

1112
01:16:26,624 --> 01:16:30,502
But he comes to see her anyway.
And I forget why, but...

1113
01:16:30,670 --> 01:16:35,382
Oh, it's so amazing when he comes to see her.

1114
01:16:35,549 --> 01:16:39,511
Because he doesn't even notice
that she doesn't get up to say hello.

1115
01:16:39,679 --> 01:16:43,098
And he's very bitter.

1116
01:16:43,266 --> 01:16:48,728
You think he's just going
to walk out the door
and never know why.

1117
01:16:48,896 --> 01:16:51,273
She's just lying there, you know.

1118
01:16:51,440 --> 01:16:57,070
Like, on the couch with this
blanket over her shrivelled
little legs.

1119
01:16:57,571 --> 01:16:58,989
And...

1120
01:16:59,156 --> 01:17:01,658
Are you all right?
She's fine.

1121
01:17:01,826 --> 01:17:05,578
And suddenly, he goes, "I saw the painting"

1122
01:17:05,746 --> 01:17:09,040
And he, like, goes to the bedroom.

1123
01:17:09,208 --> 01:17:11,543
And he looks, and he comes out and looks at her.

1124
01:17:11,711 --> 01:17:16,715
And he kind of just...
They know and hug and it's so...

1125
01:17:17,675 --> 01:17:21,636
That's a chick's movie.
I would say so.

1126
01:17:21,804 --> 01:17:25,140
What kind of a person would write
to someone they heard on the radio?

1127
01:17:25,308 --> 01:17:27,684
I got hundreds of letters
from women all over the country.

1128
01:17:27,852 --> 01:17:28,935
Desperate women.

1129
01:17:29,103 --> 01:17:32,564
Just because someone is looking
for a nice guy, it doesn't make
them desperate.

1130
01:17:32,732 --> 01:17:34,024
How about rapacious
and love-starved?

1131
01:17:34,191 --> 01:17:35,233
No.

1132
01:17:35,401 --> 01:17:37,610
It's easier to be killed
by a terrorist than to
find a husband

1133
01:17:37,778 --> 01:17:40,238
after the age of 40...
That is absolutely untrue!

1134
01:17:40,406 --> 01:17:42,782
Right, honey. Right.

1135
01:17:42,950 --> 01:17:44,784
Well, I'm not looking
for a mail-order bride.

1136
01:17:44,952 --> 01:17:48,955
I just want somebody
that I can have a decent
conversation with over dinner.

1137
01:17:49,123 --> 01:17:52,834
You know, without it falling down
into weepy tears over some movie
that she just saw.

1138
01:17:53,002 --> 01:17:54,461
She's very emotional.

1139
01:17:54,628 --> 01:17:56,296
Although, I cried at the end of The Dirty Dozen.

1140
01:17:56,464 --> 01:17:57,881
Well, who didn't?
Jim Brown was throwing

